A measure of the risk profile of your account. The risk control status is divided into 4 levels: Safe, Medium, Warning, and Dangerous.\\n\\nSafe: No Financing.\\n\\nMedium: Financing has been used, equity balance value is above initial margin requirement, based on the current leverage level, the higher the leverage, the higher the risk.\\n\\nWarning: Equity balance value is below initial margin requirement but still above maintenance margin. At the moment, purchasing power has been exhausted and no new positions can be opened; please pay attention to market changes to prevent margin calls in the account.\\n\\nDanger: Equity balance value is below maintenance margin requirement. In this case, you must deposit to fulfill margin call before 15:00 on the same day according to the \\\"Margin Call Amount\\\" or take the initiative to close some positions to lower your risk level. Otherwise, your positions will be forced liquidated to fulfill Margin Call. The broker has the discretion as to the stock, price and volume put up for sell at anytime after cut-off time on force-selling day. Please pay attention to indicators such as risk control status and leverage.\\n\\nEquity Balance：The sum of cash balance and total market value of the stocks held.\\n\\nInitial Margin：The margin required for financing transactions is calculated according to a certain percentage of the market value of the stocks held. When the equity balance value is less than the initial margin requirement, the purchasing power is exhausted and new positions cannot be opened.\\n\\nMaintenance Margin：Maintenance margin requirement = account holdings market value × account holding asset maintenance margin ratio. When the equity balance value is less than the maintenance margin requirement, the account will be \\\"dangerous\\\" status, and some stocks need to be liquidated or further deposit is required.

\"Moving averages are usually calculated to identify the trend direction of a stock. It helps to smooth out the price data to mitigate the impacts of random and short-term fluctuations over a specific time period. MA5, MA10, MA20 and MA60 means the moving average of 5 days, 10 days, 20 days and 60 days.\u0020\u0020\nMA=sum of n days\' stock price / n\"

"1. When the stock price is above the BBI, means a bull market.
2. When the stock price is below the BBI, means a bear market.
3. In the bearish market, if the closing price downward cross the BBI, indicates a selling signal.
4. In the bullish market, if the closing price upward cross the BBI, indicates a buying signal."

"1. 0-20 stands for top area, 80-100 stands for bottom area.
2. When WR below 20 is overbought, shows a selling signal.
3. When WR above 80 is oversold, shows a buying signal.
4. An overbought or oversold doesn't mean the price will reverse. Overbought simply means the price is near the highs of its recent range, and oversold means the price is in the lower end of its recent range.
5. Can be used to generate trade signals when the price and the indicator move out of overbought or oversold territory."

\"KDJ indicator is known as the random index. It is a technical indicator based on the highest price, lowest price and closing price to analyze and predict changes in stock trends and price patterns in a traded asset. KDJ indicator is a very practical technical indicator which is most commonly used in market trend analysis of short-term stock.\n\nrsv=(closing price-lowest price in n days)/(highest price in n days -lowest price in n days)*100\"

\"The relative strength index (RSI) is a momentum indicator that measures the magnitude of recent price changes to evaluate overbought or oversold conditions. \nAlways take 6, 12, 24 as suitable time period.\"

1.D over 80 is overbought and below 20 is oversold. J over 100 is overbought and below 0 is oversold.
2.Always buy in the oversold area and sell in the overbought area.
3.K>D means the upward trend and K<D means the downward trend. When K line upward crosses the D line, it shows the signal of buying. When K line downward crosses the D line, it shows the signal of selling.
4.Negative divergence occurs when price is moving higher but the KDJ is moving lower, indicates a lower price in the future, and vice versa.
5.The KDJ may provide false signals at times when the market is flat.
The RSI value is normally distributed between 0-100. When RSI > 80%, it is regarded as overbought; when RSI < 20%, it is regarded as oversold.

The homeopathic index is an index that measures whether the stock price has exceeded the normal distribution range. It is a special kind of overbought and oversold indicators, and fluctuates between positive infinity and negative infinity.

\"1. When CCI>﹢100, it indicates that the stock price has entered the overbought zone. The abnormal phenomenon of stock price should be paid more attention.\n2. When CCI <-100, it indicates that the stock price has entered the oversold zone. Investors can buy stocks on dips.\n3. When the CCI is between [-100, +100], it indicates that the stock price is in the normal range of narrow oscillation consolidation, and investors should mainly wait and see.\"
Similar to MA index, when short-term EMA upward crosses the long-term EMA, shows a buying signal, vice versa.

\"On-balance volume(OBV) is a technical trading indicator that uses volume flow to predict directions of stock prices. ﻿\nWhen the price goes up while the OBV goes down, means the stock price cannot maintain upward trend and shows a selling signal.\nWhen the price shows a slight decrease while the OBV goes up, means stock price may increase and shows a buying signal.\"

\"On-balance volume(OBV) is a technical trading indicator that uses volume flow to predict directions of stock prices.\nStarting from the first day of listing, if the total daily trading volume of stocks is accumulated daily and the trading price of the day exceeds the expected closing price in the past, the OBV of the day of transaction will be added, otherwise the OBV of the day of transaction of the day will be subtracted.\"
MAVOL is moving average of total trading volume.

"1. MACD is often displayed with a histogram which shows the distance between the MACD and its signal line. When the number of the histogram equals 0, shows the signal of buying or selling.
2. The MACD has a positive value when the short-term EMA is above the long-term EMA and a negative value when the short-term EMA is below the long-term EMA.
3. MACD triggers technical signals when it crosses above (to buy) or below (to sell) its signal line.
4. If the MACD is above the signal line, the histogram will be above the MACD’s baseline and shows a bullish market, and vice versa.

MACD is a lagging indicator, for the reason that all of the data used in MACD is based on the historical price action of the stock. It is a long-term indicator and may show wrong signals when the stock price fluctuates frequently. When use the MACD indicator, traders need to put other indicators into considerations."

"Moving Average Convergence Divergence (MACD) is a trend-following momentum indicator that shows the relationship between two EMAs of a security’s price. 
DIF=short-term EMA - long-term EMA
DEA=M days EMA of DIF
MACD=2*(DIF-DEA)
-This can help traders decide when to enter, add to, or exit a position. "

"A Bollinger Band is a technical analysis tool defined by an upper and lower band(positive and negative standard deviations) away from a middle band (always 20 days' SMA) of a security's price.It can be used to generate oversold or overbought signals.

Middle band: N days' simple moving average
Upper band: middle band + 2*standard deviation
Lower band: middle band - 2*standard deviation"

The Directional Movement Indicator (DMI) is a technical tool for assessing price direction and strength.The PDI measures how strongly price moves upward, and the MDI measures how strongly price moves downward.
When the short-term MAVOL upward crosses the long-term MAVOL, shows a buying signal. When the short-term MAVOL downward crosses the long-term MAVOL, shows a selling signal.
\"An exponential moving average (EMA) is a moving average that places a greater weight on the recent data points. \nTraders always take 5, 10 and 20 as time period for moving averages.\n\"

"WR is a type of momentum indicator that moves between 0 and -100 and measures overbought and oversold levels. 

WR=(highest price in n days -closing price)/(highest price in n days - lowest price in n days)*100

WR=(Hn—C)÷(Hn—Ln)×100
n: is the trading period set by the trader
C: The latest closing price on day n
Hn: the highest price in the past n days
Ln: the lowest price in the past n days"
Bull and Bear Index(BBI), is an indicator of weighted average of closing price moving averages with different days.
